<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
    <p xml:id="Aink218-kilavi"> talaimakaṉ varaivu vēṇṭi viṭat tamar maṟutta vaḻi yatu kēṭṭ iḵt eṉṉāṅkol eṉṟ āṟṟāḷ ākiya talaimakaṭkut tōḻi taṉakku naṟkuṟi ceyyakkaṇṭu kaṭitiṉ vantu varaivāṉ eṉac colliyatu.  </p>
      <p xml:lang="en"> The confidante telling the heroine, “He will come quickly and marry [you]”, looking at the good sign for her who became unable to bear, saying “what will happen?” upon hearing that [her] people have refused as the hero desired marriage and left. </p>
      </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink218">
<l>nuṇṇēr puruvatta kaṇṇu māṭu</l>
<l>mayirvār muṉkai vaḷaiyuñ ceṟūuṅ</l>
<l>kaḷiṟukōṭ piḻaitta katañciṟan teḻupuli</l>
<l>yeḻutaru maḻaiyiṟ kuḻumum</l>
<l>peruṅka ṉāṭaṉ varuṅko laṉṉāy</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>[Your] eyes, [adorned] with fine and beautiful brows, twitch. </l>
<l>The bangles on [your] forearms, lined with hair, become tight. </l>
<l rend="space">The man from the land on the mountain, </l>
<l>where a tiger which arisen in heightened fury, </l>
<l>from which a male elephant has fled,</l>
<l>roars like the rising clouds –</l>
<l>won’t he come, Mother? </l>

      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
